# StaffySoft Portfolio — environment variables reference.
#
# Copy to `.env.local` to override values locally (`.env.local` is gitignored).
# In production these are configured as Vercel Environment Variables
# (Production + Preview) on all portfolio deploys — they are NOT read from this
# file at deploy time. This file just documents what the app looks for.

# ── Client-side (NEXT_PUBLIC_*, inlined into the bundle at build time) ───────

# Base URL for StaffySoft Core's accounts app. Each product's "Add to account"
# CTA deep-links to `${NEXT_PUBLIC_STAFFYSOFT_ACCOUNTS_URL}/add?product=<id>`,
# and the header's "Sign in" CTA / account switcher point at the same host.
# Defaults to https://accounts.staffysoft.com (a Vercel alias for the Core
# project) when unset, so local builds work with no config.
NEXT_PUBLIC_STAFFYSOFT_ACCOUNTS_URL=https://accounts.staffysoft.com

# ── Server-side (signed-in header, #15 — never NEXT_PUBLIC) ──────────────────

# Per-product secret for Core's SDK API (x-api-key), as registered in Core's
# products table. Required for the signed-in header: without it the session
# routes degrade gracefully and every visitor is a guest.
CORE_API_KEY=

# Product key the portfolio is registered under in Core. Default: portfolio
# CORE_PRODUCT_KEY=portfolio

# Core base URL for server-to-server SDK calls. Defaults to
# NEXT_PUBLIC_STAFFYSOFT_ACCOUNTS_URL (then https://accounts.staffysoft.com);
# set only if the SDK host ever diverges from the accounts app.
# CORE_BASE_URL=https://accounts.staffysoft.com

# Domain of Core's shared SSO cookie, needed to clear it on sign-out. Must
# match Core's own CORE_SSO_COOKIE_DOMAIN. `.staffysoft.com` in production;
# leave unset in local dev, where the cookie is host-only.
# CORE_SSO_COOKIE_DOMAIN=.staffysoft.com
